Authorization
• The DIA Board hereby authorizes the CEO to take all actions necessary to effectuate the intent of this Resolution including execution of an agreement for services or functional equivalent.
• The expenditure of $28,000.00 payable to Downtown Vision, Inc., for events, marketing, and communications services during FY 25-26.

Actors
• DIA Board
• CEO
• City Council
• DVI (Downtown Vision, Inc.)

Financial details
• One-time contribution of $28,000 from General Fund Advertising & Promotion.
• Approximately $8,000 will support hosting and technical functionality of the Development Map and Find Property platforms.
• The remaining $20,000 will support event planning, marketing, communications, and related as-needed services.

Property
• Downtown Vision, Inc. (recipient)

Timeline
• This Resolution shall become effective on the date it is signed by the Chair of the DIA Board.

Conditions
• Services must be within the Downtown boundaries.
• Agreements do not require further City Council approval if they do not exceed one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000).

Next steps
• Execution of an agreement for services or functional equivalent.

Authorization
• The DIA Board is authorized by the Jacksonville City Council through Ordinance 2020-0527-E.

Actors
• DIA is the Community Redevelopment Agency and Economic Development entity for Downtown Jacksonville; 
  Chief Executive Officer of the Downtown Investment Authority; Carmen Godwin, Managing Member;
  Rafael Godwin, Managing Member.

Financial details
• Total Development Costs: $4,085,200; Equity: $625,000 (15.3% of Underwritten TDC); City Funding:
  No more than $1,620,655 through the Northbank Downtown Redevelopment Trust Fund.

Property
• Address: 44 W Monroe Street; approximately 2,700 square feet of retail space proposed for retail/cafe
  space with sidewalk activation within City Center, Downtown Jacksonville.

Timeline
• Not specified in document

Conditions
• Work proposed must be reviewed and approved by the Planning and Development Department;
  Proposed incentive structure and funding will be subject to further approvals by the Jacksonville
  City Council.

Next steps
• The Chief Executive Officer is hereby authorized to execute the contracts and documents and otherwise
  take all necessary action in connection therewith to effectuate the purposes of this Resolution.
